1513 The above appropriation includes funds to pay salary supplements and related
1514 benefit costs for Nationally Board-Certified Teachers (NBCT) and other costs
1515 of the program. Supplement amounts will be determined by the availability of
1516 funds based on the number of National Board Certified Teachers. (1) The
1517 state of Alabama will provide an annual supplement of $5,000 to any NBCT
1518 that is employed full-time in a public K-12 school and is properly certified
1519 by the state of Alabama. The existing eligibility criteria will apply: (a)
1520 NBCTs employed on a less than full-time contract on October 1 will receive a
1521 pro-rata share of the salary supplement. (b) NBCTs employed full-time after
1522 October 1 will receive a pro-rata share of the salary supplement. (c) NBCTs
1523 who earn National Board Certification in another state and are teaching
1524 full-time in Alabama on October 1 and are properly certified by the state of
1525 Alabama will receive the annual salary stipend. (d) NBCTs employed as a
1526 substitute are not eligible for the salary supplement. (e) NBCTs who are on
1527 leave of absence for more than half a school year will receive a prorated
1528 amount based on the number of months worked during the school year. (f)
1529 NBCTs will receive the salary supplement each year of the valid period of
1530 the certificate unless the Alabama Legislature declines to make the annual
1531 appropriation. (g) NBCTs must renew their certificate by the year of the
1532 certificate's expiration in order to continue receiving the salary
1533 supplement. (h) NBCTs employed in the final year of the certificate valid
1534 period will receive a prorated amount based on the number of months worked
1535 covered in that valid period. (i) NBCTs who leave after October 1 will be
1536 eligible for a prorated amount based on the months served. (j) NBCTs must
