2042 To be distributed as grants to monuments to commemorate historical events
2043 and places, historical skills centers, cultural heritage parks, historic
2044 sites, commissions, boards, agencies, and authorities that are not owned,
2045 operated, or otherwise under the control of the Alabama Historical
2046 Commission or other state agencies. Grants will be awarded to entities that
2047 reflect a historical education-based mission and concentrate on historical
2048 educational programming. Preference shall be given to: (1) any property
2049 constructed prior to 1840 that is listed in or eligible for the National
2050 Register of Historic Places and that are publicly owned and accessible to
2051 the public; or (2) any property in Alabama built in 1943 or before, and is
2052 listed in or eligible for the National Register of Historic Places or any
2053 property built after 1943 that significantly contributed to the civil rights
2054 movement. The first three grants shall be reserved for Old State Bank for
2055 $200,000, Huntsville Historical Depot for $100,000, and Mt. Pinson
2056 Presbyterian Church for $75,000. Remaining grant amounts shall not exceed
2057 $100,000 for any one entity and must be used within two years of receiving
2058 the grant. Grants will not be awarded to any entity receiving funding
2059 directly or indirectly from the Education Trust Fund or the General Fund nor
2060 may grants be awarded to any private or for-profit business or organization.
